{"article_id":"umbmkCEHgp6tXBkb","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"North Korea has said","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"it is considering carrying out missile strikes on the US Pacific territory of Guam .","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"The North 's official news agency said on Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"the plan involved firing medium-to-long-range rockets at Guam ,","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"where US strategic bombers are based .","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"US Secretary of State Rex Tillerson ,","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"flying into Guam ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"there was no imminent threat from North Korea .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"He also defended President Donald Trump ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"who on Tuesday threatened Pyongyang with `` fire and fury '' .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"Mr Tillerson said","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"that North Korean leader Kim Jong-un did not understand diplomatic language ,","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"and a strong message was needed","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"that he would understand .","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"`` I think","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"the president just wanted to be clear to the North Korean regime","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"that the US ... will defend itself and its allies , ''","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"On Wednesday , Mr Trump tweeted","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"that the US nuclear arsenal was `` more powerful than ever before '' ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"but added","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"he was hopeful","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"`` we will never have to use this power '' .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"The recent exchanges mark a sharp rise in rhetoric between Washington and Pyongyang ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"but China has urged calm .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"A foreign ministry statement","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"quoted by Reuters","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"called on all sides to avoid words or actions","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"which might escalate the situation","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"and to make greater efforts","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"to resolve the issue via talks .","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"The UN recently approved further economic sanctions on North Korea ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"which","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"Pyongyang said","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"were a `` violent violation of our sovereignty '' ,","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"warning","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"the US would `` pay a price '' .","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"On Wednesday , the official KCNA news agency said","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"North Korea was `` carefully examining the operational plan","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"for making an enveloping fire at the areas around Guam ''","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"using its domestically made medium-to-long-range Hwasong-12 missiles .","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"The news agency reported a military statement","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"issued on Tuesday ,","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"which probably came in response to US military drills in Guam .","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"However , there has been no indication","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"that any attack on Guam by North Korea is imminent .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"In a message to the public , the governor of Guam Eddie Baza Calvo said","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"there was currently `` no threat '' to the island and the Marianas archipelago ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"but that Guam was `` prepared for any eventuality '' .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"North Korea 's statement is the latest stage in a heating up of rhetoric and tension .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"Pyongyang ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"which has tested nuclear devices five times ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"launched two intercontinental ballistic missiles","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"( ICBMs )","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"in July ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"claiming","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"it now had the ability","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"to hit mainland US .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"On Tuesday , media reports in the US claimed","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"the North had achieved its goal","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"of making a nuclear warhead small enough","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"to fit inside its missiles .","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"While not confirmed ,","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"this was seen as one of the last obstacles","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"to North Korea being a fully nuclear-armed state .","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"A report in the Washington Post ,","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"citing US intelligence officials ,","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"suggested","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"North Korea was developing nuclear weapons","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"capable of hitting the US at a much faster rate","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"than expected .","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"A Japanese government defence white paper also said","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"the weapons programme had `` advanced considerably ''","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"and that North Korea possibly now had nuclear weapons .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"In response , President Trump warned North Korea to stop threatening the US ,","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"they would be `` met with fire and fury","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"like the world has never seen '' .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"However , veteran US Senator John McCain was sceptical about Mr Trump 's statement ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"he was `` not sure","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"that President Trump is ready to act '' . '","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"Scary ' situation","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"- BBC 's Yogita Limaye in Seoul , South Korea","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"On the streets of Seoul , barely 50km","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"( 30 miles )","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"from the border with North Korea , the latest developments have drawn mixed reactions .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"Kim Seong-su , 62 , said","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"he thought","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"Pyongyang was bluffing","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"to preserve its regime","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"and justify its nuclear programme .","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"But others are more concerned .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"Yeon Eui-sook says","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"she finds the situation scary .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"`` I hope","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"everyone can live in peace .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"Kim Jong-un keeps doing this","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"and making us worry , ''","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"she said .","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"Analysts say","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"the language from Pyongyang always gets more aggressive in August ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"when the US and South Korea conduct joint military exercises .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"But this time","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"- with a US president","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"who also uses strong words -","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"the confrontation is getting even fiercer than usual .","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"North Korea had reacted angrily","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"after the fresh sanctions were announced on Saturday by the UN ,","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"in an attempt to pressure it into giving up its nuclear ambitions .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"The sanctions aim to reduce North Korea 's export revenues by a third .","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"KCNA said","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"North Korea would retaliate","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"and make `` the US pay a price ''","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"for drafting the new measures .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"It called the sanctions a `` violent violation of our sovereignty '' ,","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"the news agency said .","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"Meanwhile on Wednesday the UK Foreign Office said","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"it would `` continue to work with the US and our international partners","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"to maintain pressure on North Korea '' .","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"`` We have been consistently clear and forthright in our condemnation of North Korea 's destabilising and illegal behaviour ,","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"including through support for UN Security Council resolutions","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"to bring in sanctions","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"that will limit North Korea 's ability","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"to pursue its nuclear weapons programme , ''","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"a spokesman said .","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"A spokesman for Germany 's foreign ministry ,","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"quoted by AFP ,","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"said","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"it was watching the situation `` with the greatest concern ''","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"and called on all sides to use restraint .","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"The 541sq km","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"( 209 sq miles )","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"volcanic and coral island in the Pacific between the Philippines and Hawaii .","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"It is a `` non-incorporated '' US territory , with a population of about 163,000 .","depth":6},{"id":136,"text":"That means people","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"born in Guam","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"are US citizens ,","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"have an elected governor and House Representative ,","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"but can not vote for a president in US national elections .","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"US military bases cover about a quarter of the island .","depth":5},{"id":142,"text":"About 6,000 personnel are based there","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"and there are plans","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"to move in thousands more .","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"It was a key US base in World War Two ,","depth":4},{"id":146,"text":"and remains a vital staging post for US operations ,","depth":5},{"id":147,"text":"giving access to potential flashpoints like the South China Sea , the Koreas and the Taiwan Straits .","depth":5},{"id":148,"text":"Get news from the BBC in your inbox , each weekday morning","depth":1}],"relations":[{"parent":297,"left":296,"right":148,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":296,"left":280,"right":295,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":280,"left":256,"right":279,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":172,"right":255,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":167,"right":171,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":167,"left":153,"right":166,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":150,"right":152,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":152,"left":2,"right":151,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":156,"right":165,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":156,"left":155,"right":8,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":155,"left":154,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":154,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":157,"right":164,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":160,"right":163,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":11,"right":159,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":159,"left":12,"right":158,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":158,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":162,"right":18,"relation":"at